        "timestamp": "2017-09-13 12:50:12.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThanks Daniel, good work.  I think we talked error case handling will come later, case, aai query fails or don't get enough info, correct?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "6bb0a5ba3bf4d4ae85a487a614750c3b95d01b80",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1677,
          "name": "Daniel Cruz",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "dc443y@att.com",
          "username": "dc443y"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-09-13 12:59:34.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Thanks Daniel, good work.  I think we talked error case handling\n > will come later, case, aai query fails or don't get enough info,\n > correct?\n\n > Thanks Daniel, good work.  I think we talked error case handling\n > will come later, case, aai query fails or don't get enough info,\n > correct?\n\nRight, for now what happens is if it does not find the proper vnf-id it well be nulled out and not sent in the request but the request is still sent. This will result in APPC giving us a failure in which Policy will send an operation failure and then a final failure. In the future we should not send a request if any information is missing and retract everything from memory in my opinion. This will be for all actors, not just APPC.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
